{"id":38426,"date":"2022-11-01T19:20:32","date_gmt":"2022-11-01T15:20:32","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38426"},"modified":"2023-02-23T11:27:08","modified_gmt":"2023-02-23T07:27:08","slug":"powerful-dua-nahar-wa-layl","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/11\/01\/powerful-dua-nahar-wa-layl\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Dua: Powerful supplication to Allah, morning and evening"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Ayyub reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<b>Whoever says ten times when he awakens in the morning, \u2018There is no God but Allah, alone without any partners to Him. He owns the dominion and for Him is all praise. He gives life and causes death, for He has power over all things,\u2019 then Allah will record ten good times for each time he said it, Allah will erase ten sins by it, he will be raised by Allah ten degrees, it will be as if he has freed ten slaves, he will be guarded from the beginning of the day until its end, and he will not act on that day with anything else to overcome it. If he says it in the evening, then he will have the same.<\/b>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 23578<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em><strong>Sahih<\/strong> <\/em>(authentic) according to Al-Arna&#8217;ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0623\u064e\u064a\u064f\u0651\u0648\u0628\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0635\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062d\u0650\u064a\u0646\